claim.claim-text:
1. A method for operating a Mobile Station (MS) in a sleep mode state in a wireless communication system, the method comprising:
responsive to failing to receive a traffic indication message and unicast data during a listening window, transmitting a request message to a Base Station (BS) to inquire a location of a next scheduled listening window;
receiving a response message that is unicasted in response to the request message;
performing sleep cycle synchronization by using synchronization information included in the response message; and
determining whether an emergency alert service-related message is transmitted by using emergency alert service-related information included in the response message.
